title: Cloak golden gate — re-darkening when the cloak is retrieved
story: cloak-of-darkness
description: Divergence 2 from Firth's original — `dark while the player
  has the velvet cloak` is a derived property, so the bar re-darkens
  whenever the player regains the cloak (and re-lights when they shed it),
  including in place inside the bar. ADR-210 AC-1 golden gate (frozen
  2026-07-10).

---

# Hang the cloak first: the bar starts lit
> west
> remove cloak
> hang cloak on hook
[OK: contains "put the velvet cloak on the brass hook"]

> east
> south
[OK: contains "Foyer Bar"]
[OK: contains "message scrawled in the sawdust"]

# Retrieve the cloak and come back: the bar is dark again, and this
# first dark entry trips the stumble rule
> north
> west
> take cloak
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> east
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> look
[OK: contains "pitch dark"]

# In-place recomputation: dropping the cloak inside the bar lights it...
> drop cloak
[OK: contains "Dropped"]

> look
[OK: contains "much rougher than you'd have guessed"]

# ...and picking it back up darkens it again (no stumble — no entry occurred)
> take cloak
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> look
[OK: contains "pitch dark"]
[OK: not contains "Blundering"]
